<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="U" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Uncle2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Uncle,</orth> a verb coined by York in <bibl n="shak. r2 2.3.87" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 3, 87</bibl>: <emph>grace me no grace, nor u. me no uncle;</emph> i. e. do not call me uncle.
